article.headline: Norfolk St. 59, Howard 44
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Michael Deloach scored 16 points and Corey Lyons had 15 to lead Norfolk State to a 59-44 victory over Howard on Monday. The score was tied twice early in the game, but a layup by Chidi Okoli gave the Spartans (10-10, 6-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) the lead for good six minutes in. The Spartans led 32-18 at the half. Deloach went 8-of-12 from the field and had four rebounds and Lyons had nine rebounds for the Spartans. Randy Hampton led the Bison (5-17, 2-6) with 13 points and Paul Kirkpatrick added nine points and six rebounds. Norfolk State outshot Howard 37 percent to 35 percent and outrebounded the Bison 45-33.
